  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">2021 oPt Emergency Appeal - West Bank - Emergency Cash Assistance</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In 2021, UNRWA plans to provide unconditional and non-restricted cash assistance through its e-card modality to an estimated 24,128 abject poor refugee individuals in the West Bank, inside and outside of the 19 refugee camps. This modality provides cash to vulnerable refugees who live on less than two dollars a day, through bank debit cards in partnership with the Bank of Palestine. Beneficiaries are targeted following assessments by UNRWA social workers. The poverty level of the households is assessed using a Proxy Means Test Formula (PMTF). Each household identified receives 125 New Israeli Shekels (ILS) (approx. US$ 35) per person per quarter.</narrative>
  </description>
